  <!-- Explanation Comments -->
  <!--
    WaySave-2.0 App Prototype
    -------------------------
    This is a fully self-contained HTML app prototype for discovering NYC activities.
    It includes:
      - Splash screen with logo and tap-to-start
      - User survey collecting name, age group, borough, and interests
      - Activity discovery with category filtering and expandable cards
      - Sponsored cards and banner ads clearly marked
      - Live Events section highlighting current NYC happenings
      - Savie AI assistant bubble with chat UI and placeholder AI responses
      - Directions link using Apple Maps URLs
      - Responsive and mobile-friendly layout
      - iOS web app icon and metadata for home screen bookmarking

    To run:
      1. Save this entire HTML code into a file named 'index.html'.
      2. Open the file locally in any modern browser or deploy to GitHub Pages.
      3. Tap the splash screen to start.
      4. Fill out the survey and hit 'Find Activities'.
      5. Explore activities, filter categories, and chat with Savie.

    This app is a front-end-only prototype with static data and no backend.
    Future improvements could include real AI integration and live data feeds.
  -->

